# Source‑anchored answers

- When referencing project behavior, base your answer on concrete evidence from the codebase, config, tests, or docs you have read.

- Prefer quoting or summarizing real code or config over describing hypothetical code.

- If you cannot find the relevant code or documentation, say so and mark your statement as [uncertain] rather than assuming how it might work.